Because the parameter of [forEach(...)][1] is a [Consumer][2].
```
myBean -&gt; {
  myMethod(myBean);
}
```
The above is an implementation of consumer as lambda function.

`Consumer.accept()` does not throw exceptions, so you have to handle it in some way - possibly catch and rethrow as unchecked exception.

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Iterable.html#forEach-java.util.function.Consumer-
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/function/Consumer.html

